    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gu-grow-bmp-route-leak-detection-05.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-gu-grow-bmp-route-leak-detection-05.txt</link>
        <title>"BMP for BGP Route Leak Detection", Yunan Gu, China Telecom, Di Ma, Shunwan Zhuang</title>
        <dc:date>2021-07-10T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>According to Route-Leak Problem Definition [RFC7908], Route leaks refer to the case that the delivery range of route advertisements is beyond the expected range.  For many current security protection solutions, the ISPs (Internet Service Providers) are focusing on finding ways to prevent the happening of BGP [RFC4271] route leaks. However, the real-time route leak detection if any occurs is important as well, and serves as the basis for leak mitigation.  This document extends the BGP Monitoring Protocol (BMP) [RFC7854] to provide a routing security scheme suitable for ISPs to detect BGP route leaks at the prefix level.</description>
    </item>
